article.headline: Jacksonville 71, Lipscomb 66
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Haminn Quaintance posted his eighth double-double of the season with 18 points and 11 rebounds, leading Jacksonville to a 71-66 win over Lipscomb on Thursday night. The Dolphins (13-12, 8-10 Atlantic Sun) trailed by as many as 13 points in the second half before rallying. A 15-4 run brought them within 51-49 with 9:19 left, and Jacksonville closed the game on an 8-0 run. Chad Hartman shot 8-for-8 from the field and led the Bisons with 18 points. Jason Jackson added 14 for Lipscomb (7-18, 4-13), which was held scoreless for the final 2:45. It was the fifth time this season Jacksonville won a game in which it trailed by double digits in the second half. The Dolphins, who started the Atlantic Sun season at 1-8, have now won seven of their last nine conference games. Aubrey Conerly and David Lee scored 14 points each for the Dolphins. Conerly tied the game at 66 with a 3-pointer, and Lee's layup with 45 seconds left put Jacksonville ahead for good. Lipscomb fell to 1-8 in conference road games.
